However, restrictions on abortion have been observed to raise the number of clandestine abortions, which are often unsafe and often lead to serious and fatal obstetric complications. The Maternal Mortality Ratio in CAR (1500 deaths per 100.000 delivery) is among the highest in the world and illegal abortion is a key factor for the high MMR [16].

The main health services provided at the cellular level are vaccinations, treatments, and maternal and child healthcare related to obstetric emergencies. Attention given also to the pregnant and lactating women and to children up till 5 years old. The rural community health workers are often unpaid and it is very difficult to meet the expectations of the beneficiaries as the majority, especially older adults, sometimes do not believe in vaccination as it is considered part of a colonialist repressive action. Women also do not want to involve their husband in their pregnancy care, which is meant to take place in a respected and highly valued way.

To satisfy the most diverse client needs through different programs including maternal and child health, has to be done in a proper way, based on the community needs and opinions and practiced in a communicative and participatory attitude.
